content.problem:
A sphere has radius 10. A plane intersects the sphere 6 units 
from the center. Find the radius of the resulting small circle.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 % Cross-section view
 (0,0) circle (3);
 (-2.4,1.8) – (2.4,1.8);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (3pt);
 at (0,0) {$O$};

 % Distance to plane
 (0,0) – (0,1.8);
 at (0,0.9) {6};

 % Radius of sphere
 (0,0) – (2.4,1.8);
 at (1.2,0.9) {10};

 % Radius of small circle
 (0,2.2) – (2.4,2.2);
 at (1.2,2.2) {$r$};
tikzpicture
center

content.text:
{3}$ 
(think ``four-thirds'') and $r^3$ (cubed, since we're measuring 
three-dimensional space).}
